fig.sd-panel:
The following properties of Schaffer collateral-CA1 synaptic responses were recorded from wt and NPC1nmf164 mice. A. Basal synaptic transmission expressed as mean ± SEM EPSP slope (n= 9 slices from 5 WT mice and n=8 slices from 5 NPC1nmf164 mice, all mice 10 week-old, unpaired Student t test, * p150μA = 0.0368, p200μA = 0.0138);
B. Mean ± SEM fibre volley amplitude (n=10 slices from 5 WT mice and n= 7 slices from 5 NPC1nmf164 mice, all mice 10 week-old);
C. Mean ± SEM paired pulse facilitation (n=11 slices from 5 WT mice and n=10 slices from 5 NPC1nmf164 mice, all mice 10 week-old, unpaired Student t test, **p = 0.0011);
D. LTP expressed as mean ± SEM percentage of EPSP slope over baseline (n=7 slices form 5 WT mice for WT and n=10 slices from 5 NPC1nmf164 mice, all mice 10 week-old, unpaired Student t test, ***p < 0.0001 in the last 10 min recording)
